Tim Waugh wrote:
> Not if the -k option isn't given to modprobe in the post-install rule.
> Anyway, the MOD_USE_COUNT should take care of that, surely?
No it doesn't. USB is hotplug, and rmmod hostcontrollerdriver
in effect does the same as unplugging all devices on that bus,
i.e. is possible even if it is in use.
